WARNING: This will be long and transparent. Can you believe we‚Äôve been ‚Äúhome‚Äù for almost six months?! I‚Äôm still a bit in denial that our days of adventure and exploring are doneüöê

When we returned to California, it was never our intention to end our travels but RV repairs took forever and before we knew it after a series of events, we decided it was best to stop and that was that. 
Transitioning back has been strange. We knew it would take time and we have given ourselves that (I am just now looking to go back to work). But also, after 8 months of posting and sharing our journey through stories every day, I kinda just felt over it. Thankful for the friendships we madeüíü, but I was kind of done sharing, done posting, and feeling a bit rebelliousüö´. Social media was and still is a blessing. It provided us an opportunity as a family to spend 24/7 exploring the countryüá∫üá∏. Days together learning about each other in a way that you only can when you are together endlessly in tiny quarters without breaks. There were hard days but if asked if we‚Äôd do it again...ABSOLUTELY. No one can take away the memories, the experiences, the joys, the hard days, the fact that WE DID IT.üôåüèºüôåüèº But bringing us back to the rebellion...we got back to California, not really homeless, but hello üëãüèº, we had sold our home. We moved in with family and we didn‚Äôt think about it at the time but that meant posting was about to become really hard. It‚Äôs not our home, not to mention the aesthetics (shag carpet and allüòÇ), but it‚Äôs just not ours to share. So to get pictures means we have to leave the house and I‚Äôm not sure how many of you are parents but going out with kids and bears everyday is no easy task. AND we we kind of just needed a rest. The last thing we want is our kids growing up and having to see a therapist because their parents made them take pictures every dayüôÑ. But it‚Äôs been a struggle because we do feel like this platform has given us the chance to share our lives and all the joy God has given us. So there it is...I‚Äôm probably being more extreme than I need to be.....continued in comments...
